<p>When I try to execute this from the backend my sp works fine but from Visual Studio <code>ExecuteScalar</code> always returns <code>false</code>. Here is my procedure.</p>  <pre><code>begin    set nocount on   declare @res bit     set @res = 0     if exists(select 1 from Documents           where intCompItemUniqid = @CompItemUniqId and                     flgActive = 1 and                     txtCompItemType = @CompItemType)                 begin                     select @res = 1                 end       select @res  end </code></pre>  <hr>  <pre><code>public static object GetScalar(string sql, object[] parms = null,CommandType commandtype= CommandType.Text)         {             string cnstringName = Utility.RetrieveAppNameFromUrl(System.Web.HttpContext.Current.Request.Url.Host);             string connectionStringValue = ConfigurationManager.ConnectionStrings[cnstringName] != null ? ConfigurationManager.ConnectionStrings[cnstringName].ConnectionString : "";               using (var connection = factory.CreateConnection())             {                 connection.ConnectionString = connectionStringValue;                  using (var command = factory.CreateCommand())                 {                     command.Connection = connection;                     command.CommandText = sql;                     command.CommandType = commandtype;                     command.SetParameters(parms);                      connection.Open();                     return command.ExecuteScalar();                 }             }         } </code></pre>